.sp
Never access \fIxs_msg_t\fR members directly, instead always use the \fIxs_msg\fR family of functions\&.
.sp .5v
.RE
.SH "RETURN VALUE"
.sp
The \fIxs_msg_close()\fR function shall return zero if successful\&. Otherwise it shall return \-1 and set \fIerrno\fR to one of the values defined below\&.
.SH "ERRORS"
.PP
\fBEFAULT\fR
